  • Current Holding (24 Jul 2025): 4,837,394 shares (4.49%)

Material Takeaways:
- UBS Group reduced its stake below the 5% substantial holding threshold, potentially signaling decreased institutional interest or portfolio rebalancing.
- No other material implications for capital structure or liquidity identified.

(Note: Detailed transactions in Appendix A reflect normal market activity; omitted for brevity per guidelines.)

1Q FY26 Performance Update Summary

Key Financial & Operational Highlights:

  • Exit run rate (ERR) of annual platform subscription revenue: NZ$16.6m (+29% YoY).
  • Total revenue: NZ$6.4m (+12% YoY), comprising:
  • Subscription revenue: NZ$4.1m (+28% YoY).
  • Transaction revenue: NZ$1.5m (-16% YoY).
  • Hardware & services: NZ$0.8m (+3% YoY).
  • Gross margin: 76% (vs. 70% pcp).
  • Cash & net receivables: NZ$11.7m (NZ$8.8m cash + NZ$2.9m net receivables, no debt).
  • Capital raising: Completed A$18m (NZ$19.6m) underwritten placement; SPP underway (target: A$2m/NZ$2.2m).

Forward Guidance Reiterated:

  • FY26 platform subscription revenue growth: ~35%+.
  • EBITDA breakeven (run-rate) expected in H2 FY26.

Material Business Update:

  • FX impact (NZD ↓7.5% vs. USD) reduced ERR by ~NZ$1.3m.
  • Two large customers shifted revenue models (self-perform transactions vs. subscriptions), expected to contribute ~NZ$0.5m in FY26 (near 100% margin).
  • Extended customer-council engagement for new North America-focused subscription modules, targeting >5x productivity gains and >2x per-seat revenue growth.

No other material information identified.

• Capital Change Notice (Performance Share Rights - PSRs)

  • PSR Issuance (2024 Grant):

    • Quantity Issued: 127,828 PSRs (4.12% of total PSRs outstanding).
    • Vesting Conditions: Three tranches tied to (1) employment tenure (31 Mar 2026), (2) TSR vs. S&P/ASX All Tech Index (40th–100th percentile), and (3) financial metrics (revenue/EBIT/FCF vs. budget).
    • Conversion: 1 PSR = 1 ordinary share ($0 exercise price).

  • PSR Issuance (2025 Grant):

    • Quantity Issued: 2,039,249 PSRs (63.07% of total PSRs outstanding).
    • Vesting Conditions: Similar to 2024 Grant but with performance period ending 31 Mar 2027.

  • Total PSRs Outstanding: 5,272,563 (including prior grants).

  • Impact: Potential dilution upon conversion; no treasury shares held.

No material trading or capital raising details identified.
